==================================================================================================================================================================
Tools to become DevOps Engineer:
1. Linux
2. Git & Github
3. Bash Scripting
4. Jenkins
5. Terraform & Ansible
6. Docker & Kubernetes
7. Any Cloud Platform 

- Getting proficient in Linux and basic scripting (Bash, Python)
- Understanding how containerization works (Docker basics)
- Familiarizing yourself with cloud fundamentals (AWS/Azure/GCP)
- Building a simple CI/CD pipeline for a personal project
- Learning version control with Git
- Understanding basic networking concepts
- Exploring infrastructure as code (starting with simple Terraform scripts)
- Setting up basic monitoring and logging for your applications

Senior DevOps engineer things to know:
1. Cloud platforms: Get really good with AWS, Azure, or Google Cloud.
2. Containers: Master Docker and Kubernetes.
3. Automation: Learn tools like Ansible and GitHub Actions/Jenkins.
4. Scripting: Improve your Python, Bash, or PowerShell skills.
5. IAC: Learn Terraform and learn it well. Get proficient at writing scalable, dynamic, and DRY infra code.
6. Monitoring: Understand how to use tools like Prometheus and Grafana. Learn to use these to set detailed logging, monitoring, and alerting.
7. Security: Learn about DevSecOps practices. Understand how to use various tools to improve the security of build and deploy processes.
8. Networking: Know the basics of how networks work in the cloud.
9. Get very good at log analysis and troubleshooting. 
10. Soft skills: Work on communication and teamwork. Get good at conflict management and negotiations.

being a senior DevOps engineer means solving complex problems and helping your team. 
Keep practicing and stay curious. The more you learn, the better you'll become.

